Governor Aminu Waziri Tambuwal of Sokoto has urged PDP youths in the state not to relent in their efforts to ensure victory of the party at this Saturday’s Governorship and House of Assembly elections. He disclosed this at the Government House Sokoto, while addressing the youths who held a rally in support of his second term bid. He enjoined them to effectively mobilize for PDP’s success at the polls. Tambuwal who was represented by the Deputy Governor, Manir Dan Iya, also called on them to guard their votes after casting their ballots at the polling stations. The governor expressed optimism that the PDP would  emerge victorious in the coming elections in the state. Guber poll: Tambuwal seeks US’ intervention Sokoto deputy Governor resigns What hope for Reps contesting governorship?